ie wichtigsten Ergebnisse der gegenwärtigen Beschäftigung mit Otto in internationaler Perspektive.  aRudolf Otto grounded his concept of religion in the experience of the sacred. His perspective offered and continues to offer a major impetus for contemporary debates in theology, the philosophy of religion, religious aesthetics, and religious studies. This volume documents important insights from contemporary readings of Otto in an international perspective.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 04. Okt 2022) 0aReligionxPhilosophy. 4aDas Heilige. 4aDas Numinose. 4aReligionsphänomenologie. 4aReligionspsychologie. 4aTheologiegeschichte. 7aRELIGION / Christian Theology / General.2bisacsh  aThe Holy.  acomparative religion.  aphenomenology.  athe Numinous.1 aAlles, Gregory D., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBarth, Roderich, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBarth, Roderich, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBarth, Ulrich, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBeinhauer-Köhler, Bärbel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBraune-Krickau, Tobias, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBuntfuß, Markus, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChoi, Jeong Hwa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDanz, Christian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDanz, Christian, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aDeuser, Hermann, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDietz, Thorsten, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aErne, Thomas, econtributor.4ctb